original: ROSENGREN, Sven Erik, Direktör, Smedslätten, f Sthlm 12/5 93 av grhdl E R o Sofia Andersson, gm Maria Silvander. Studex 11, HHS 11—13. Anst Sv Hdlsbkn 13—17, avd.ch Skandbkn 17—18, kont.ch AB Jvgsmateriel 18 —21, anst Deutsche Bank i Frankf am Main 21—24, vkst dir sed. 24 o styr.led i AB Gyllenberg & Rosengren (grund 59, imp o grhdl i ur o verktyg, repr f Revue Sport ur o Kienz-le Uhrenfabr AG Schwenningen). Styr.led Sv Urgross frn, styr.suppl Sv Grossistfrb, styr.led AB Dagsposten, styr.ordf Sv Brukshundkl, v. ordf Sv Kennelkl. Resor: Tyskl o Schweiz 18, 20, 21, 22, 25, 27, 28, 30, årl 32—41, Norge 30, Danm 31, Frankr, Holl, Ital Ung 35 36, 37, 38, Finl 39. Medarb i Sv Kennelkl :s tidskr o Tidskr Brukshunden. RVO; Sv Kennelkl :s o Sv Brukshundskl :s ftjGM, Friv Skarpskytte-frns 8. komp ftjSM; Frimurare, Sthlms-Gillet, 93 års män mfl; Sv Filatelistfrn, STF, Sv Jägarfrb. Hobbies: Jakt, kynologi, fiske, filateli. °ROSENQVIST, Frans Gustaf, Direktör, Stockholm, f Ljusterö, Sthlms l, 10/7 95 av dir J G R o Anna Westerberg. Studex NReal Sthlm 14, Schartaus 14—15. Anst v NK i Pe-trograd o Moskva 16—18, deläg i Upsala Armaturfabrik AB i Upps 19—30, i Sthlm sed. 30. °ROSENQVIST, Justus Fritjof Helmer, Fabrikör, Värnamo, f Smal Rydaholm, Jkps l, 13/1 98, gm Ada Andersson. Prakt i fi företag, start AB Nya Tråd- & Spikfabr, Värnamo, 25.
translated:
ROSENGREN, Sven Erik, Director, Smedslätten, b. Stockholm 12/5 93, son of wholesale merchant E R and Sofia Andersson, m. Maria Silvander. Completed secondary school 11th grade, attended Stockholm School of Economics 1911-1913. Employed at Swedish Bank of Commerce 1913-1917, department head at Skandinaviska Banken 1917-1918, assistant manager at AB Jvgsmateriel 1918-1921, employed at Deutsche Bank in Frankfurt am Main 1921-1924, managing director since 1924 and board member of AB Gyllenberg & Rosengren (established 1959, importer and wholesale distributor of watches and tools, representative of Revue Sport watches and Kienzle Uhrenfabr AG Schwenningen). Board member of the Swedish Watch Wholesalers, board supervisor of the Swedish Wholesalers' Association, board member of AB Dagsposten, chairman of the Swedish Working Dog Club, vice chairman of the Swedish Kennel Club. Travelled to Germany and Switzerland in 1918, 1920, 1921, 1922, 1925, 1927, 1928, and 1930, annually from 1932-1941, Norway in 1930, Denmark in 1931, France, Holland, Italy, and Hungary in 1935, 1936, 1937, and 1938, and Finland in 1939. Collaborator in the publications of the Swedish Kennel Club and Brukshunden magazine. Received the Royal Order of Vasa; awarded honorary membership in the Swedish Kennel Club and Swedish Working Dog Club; served in the Volunteer Sharpshooters' 8th Company, awarded the Military Merit Medal. Freemason, member of Sthlms-Gillet, 93rd year men's club, and more; member of the Swedish Philatelic Association, Swedish Touring Association, and Swedish Hunter Association. Hobbies: Hunting, cynology, fishing, philately.

ROSENQVIST, Frans Gustaf, Director, Stockholm, b. Ljusterö, Stockholm county, 10/7 95, son of director J G R and Anna Westerberg. Completed secondary school at NReal Sthlm 1914, attended Schartaus Business School 1914-1915. Employed at NK in Petrograd and Moscow 1916-1918, co-owner of Upsala Armaturfabrik AB in Uppsala 1919-1930, in Stockholm since 1930.

ROSENQVIST, Justus Fritjof Helmer, Manufacturer, Värnamo, b. Smal Rydaholm, Jönköping county, 13/1 98, m. Ada Andersson. Practical experience in fi companies, founded AB Nya Tråd- & Spikfabr, Värnamo, in 1925.
